momma an evolution this a poem i wrote recently in memoriam of my mom i lost her to breast cancer a couple of years ago please comment and give me feedback it would be greatly appreciated hey momma how is it up there is it really all clouds and little singin angels hey girl it s everythin god promised the clouds are my bed the angels my lullabies i miss you i don t like bein with daddy he s strict and mean i can t eat candy when i wanna i miss you too babe just hang in there he s doin all he can for you candy s not all that good for you anyway momma where are you i need you i don t understand life honey i am right here with god you ll be just fine trust me you know nobody understands life momma i do not comprehend all this hard work i always have to do sweetie you ve gotta do everything that i couldn t do achieve soar excel but it s so difficult i am damn near tired of it all there s too much pressure there s too much drama i miss you don t think of it as difficult think of it as god s challenge don t let it get to you take it and over come it that dear is the essence of life i actually had an emotional response to this hard to elicit in me these days i'm sorry for your loss and you made me feel it in your writing i'm not sure if you want me to critique this as a poem i'm not sure i could anyway the emotions would get in the way for now i'll just say good job you're not alone in your pain i haven't lost my mother but i've watched her lose hers i can only imagine The dozens The McGuire Sisters Cliff Richard Hip hop collaborations The SpongeBob SquarePants Movie Calvin and Hobbes The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Billboard Hot 100 Jon Secada Sin City EastEnders Kyle Broflovski Frankie Vaughan Babe Ruth The Amber Spyglass Sinfest Goodness and value theory The Marshall Mathers LP Prostate cancer Yoko Ono The Catcher in the Rye Harry Nilsson Friends Year of the Spider Max Martin S__ren Kierkegaard Beatles for Sale The Beatles Pakistani 